In [ ]:

Define, Train and Evaluate The Network¶

In [ ]:
model1 = models.Sequential()
model1.add(Dense(1, activation='relu', input_shape=(784,)))
model1.add(Dense(10, activation='softmax'))

model1.summary()

earlystopcb = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_accuracy', patience=3)

model1.compile(loss = 'categorical_crossentropy',
              metrics = ['accuracy'],
              optimizer = 'rmsprop')

Evaluate Activation Values¶

In [ ]:
# Extracts the outputs of the 2 layers:
layer_outputs = [layer.output for layer in model1.layers]

# Creates a model that will return these outputs, given the model input:
activation_model = models.Model(inputs=model1.input, outputs=layer_outputs)

print(f"There are {len(layer_outputs)} layers")
layer_outputs; # description of the layers

There are 2 layers

Experiment #4¶

PCA Decomposition¶

In [ ]:
pca = PCA(n_components=154)
In [ ]:
(x_train, y_train), (x_test, y_test)= tf.keras.datasets.mnist.load_data()

x_train_2 = x_train.reshape(len(x_train), x_train.shape[1] * x_train.shape[2])
x_test_2 = x_test.reshape(len(x_test), x_test.shape[1] * x_test.shape[2])

x_train_2 = x_train_2 / 255
x_test_2 = x_test_2 / 255

train_principalComponents = pca.fit_transform(x_train_2)
test_principalComponents = pca.fit_transform(x_test_2)

x_train_pca = train_principalComponents[:55000]
y_train_pca = y_train[:55000]
x_val_pca = train_principalComponents[55000:]
y_val_pca = y_train[55000:]

y_train_encoded = to_categorical(y_train_pca)
y_test_encoded = to_categorical(y_test)
y_val_encoded = to_categorical(y_val_pca)

Define, Train and Evaluate The Network¶

In [ ]:
model4 = models.Sequential()
model4.add(Dense(30, activation='relu', input_shape=(154,)))
model4.add(Dense(10, activation='softmax'))

model4.summary()

earlystopcb = EarlyStopping(monitor='loss', patience=3)

model4.compile(loss = 'categorical_crossentropy',
              metrics = ['accuracy'],
              optimizer = 'rmsprop')

Evaluate Activation Values¶

In [ ]:
# Extracts the outputs of the 2 layers:
layer_outputs = [layer.output for layer in model4.layers]

# Creates a model that will return these outputs, given the model input:
activation_model = models.Model(inputs=model4.input, outputs=layer_outputs)

print(f"There are {len(layer_outputs)} layers")
layer_outputs; # description of the layers

There are 2 layers

# Reloading data just to ensure I have fresh data
(x_train, y_train), (x_test, y_test)= tf.keras.datasets.mnist.load_data()
In [ ]:
# Quick normalizing and train/test/val splits
x_train_short = x_train[:55000]
y_train_short = y_train[:55000]
x_val = x_train[55000:]
y_val = y_train[55000:]

x_train_short = x_train_short.reshape(len(x_train_short), x_train_short.shape[1] * x_train_short.shape[2])
x_test = x_test.reshape(len(x_test), x_test.shape[1] * x_test.shape[2])
x_val = x_val.reshape(len(x_val), x_val.shape[1] * x_val.shape[2])

x_train_short = x_train_short / 255
x_test = x_test / 255
x_val = x_val / 255

y_train_encoded = to_categorical(y_train_short)
y_test_encoded = to_categorical(y_test)
y_val_encoded = to_categorical(y_val)

def plot_digit(data):
    image = data.reshape(28, 28)
    plt.imshow(image, cmap = 'hot',
               interpolation="nearest")
    plt.axis("off")

plot_digit(rnd_clf.feature_importances_)

def pair(n,size):
    x = n//size 
    y = n%size
    return x,y

Define, Train and Evaluate The Network¶

In [ ]:
model5 = models.Sequential()
model5.add(Dense(30, activation='relu', input_shape=(70,)))
model5.add(Dense(10, activation='softmax'))

model5.summary()

earlystopcb = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_accuracy', patience=3)

model5.compile(loss = 'categorical_crossentropy',
              metrics = ['accuracy'],
              optimizer = 'rmsprop')
